news.title: Belagavi: Farmers set one-week ultimatum over delay in Buda’s residential layout
news.para: The farmers who have given their land for the project are frustrated with the long wait. They have given a deadline of one week to the authority to begin the project.

news.title: LIC Housing aims to double affordable housing share in loan book in two years
news.para: "At present, affordable housing is 8-10 per cent of the portfolio, and we are targeting to take it to 20-25 per cent of the loanbook in two years," Adhikari said.

news.title: Sunac China and CIFI Holdings say projects get local government support
news.para: China's largest private property developer Country Garden , which defaulted on its offshore debt late last year, said on Saturday more than 30 of its projects had been listed as suitable for financing support from local governments.

news.title: Karnataka HC issues guidelines to prevent unauthorized constructions
news.para: Justice Suraj Govindaraj issued them after coming across a case wherein a resident of Muruguesh Palya complained about unauthorized construction encroaching upon a public road, the judge noted that though an office note dated July 27, 2023 mentions corrective measures in relation to unauthorized constructions, there are no steps indicated to prevent them.

news.title: Delhi: MCD invites public suggestions on road network plan in three unauthorised colonies
news.para: The civic body has joined hands with the Delhi Development Authority (DDA) for a pilot project on the approval to the road network plan (RNP) in the three colonies - Khirki Extension in south Delhi, Saroop Nagar Extension in north Delhi and East Azad Nagar in east Delhi.

news.title: Bombay HC permits redevelopment of Bandra building that collapsed in 1998
news.para: Govinda Tower was constructed on a Mhada-leased plot by Apex Gas Services Pvt Ltd. Initially, four floors were proposed and then three were added.

news.title: Gurugram: Buyback & rebuild offer extended to Chintels Paradiso phase-II homeowners
news.para: The company has now written to Paradiso RWA to ascertain how many homeowners are interested in the offer and sought their feedback. Demolition of towers will start after the developer gets approvals from the authorities.

news.title: NCLT admits Vadraj Cement for insolvency process
news.para: Last Friday, NCLT pronounced an order to admit Vadraj Cement, formerly known as ABG Cement, for corporate insolvency process. Adani Group, UltraTech Cement and JSW Cement may bid to acquire the debt-laden company, lenders said.

news.title: Bulandshahr: Demolition fears for 400 families in illegal colonies
news.para: The Enforcement Directorate (ED) recently seized Goyal's 58 properties estimated to be worth Rs 27 crore. The colony is one of several illegal developments allegedly done by Goyal and his associates over the past decade.

news.title: China's Country Garden says over 30 projects have local government support
news.para: China's largest private property developer said in a statement to Reuters that its projects were included on the so-called "white lists" of the provinces of Heinan, Hubei, Sichuan, Shandong and the municipality Chongqing.

news.title: Brihanmumbai civic body will monetise its properties: Municipal commissioner
news.para: The corporation will appoint a “world renowned real estate consultant” to prepare a masterplan for its leasehold and tenanted properties spread across the city.

news.title: Six farmhouses, boundary walls built on Aravali land demolished
news.para: The move comes after the directions of National Green Tribunal (NGT) to demolish illegal structures in areas that fall under sections 4 and 5 of the Punjab Land Protection Act (PLPA).

news.title: Vadodara: Himmatnagar housing scheme protesters detained, freed
news.para: Earlier, the residents had been issued notices in 2019, 2021 and twice last year. While many have vacated their houses, others are still staying there.

news.title: Property tax mopup lags as 2023-24 bills still to be issued in Mumbai
news.para: Till Jan 3, its collection stood at a mere Rs 606 crore. BMC is still to issue bills for property tax for the current financial year. Following govt directives, it has waived off property tax for units up to 500 square feet.

news.title: Kerala-RERA team inspects unregistered projects
news.para: The authority inspected the two plots of the development projects located in Anad and Nanniyode panchayat. These plots are being developed and sold without registering with the authority.

news.title: Affidavit relief for homeowners in merged areas of Pune
news.para: These forms are necessary to receive 40% property tax benefits offered by Pune Municipal Corporation (PMC) for self-occupied properties.

news.title: Having house constructed in Ludhiana? Get online building plan approval
news.para: ​Once submitted, the plan will deemed to have been approved if the official responsible for approving the plan does not raise an objection in 10 days.
